---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const dataset = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Dataset',
  '@id': 'https://prodipdata.com/ip-geolocation-database.html#dataset',
  name: 'ProdIPData IP Geolocation Database',
  description: 'Landing page for the ProdIPData IP geolocation database, release coverage, and download access.',
  url: 'https://prodipdata.com/ip-geolocation-database.html',
  isAccessibleForFree: true,
  license: 'https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/',
  creator: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'ProdIPData', url: 'https://prodipdata.com/' },
  publisher: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'ProdIPData', url: 'https://prodipdata.com/' },
  keywords: ['IP geolocation database', 'download', 'ProdIPData', 'IPv4', 'ASN', 'monthly release'],
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Free IP Geolocation Database Downloads and Release Coverage | ProdIPData"
  description="Explore ProdIPData IP geolocation database downloads with monthly CSV, Parquet, and MMDB releases, country coverage, ASN context, and registry intelligence."
  ogTitle="Free IP Geolocation Database Downloads and Release Coverage"
  canonicalPath="/ip-geolocation-database.html"
  page="guide"
  navPage="platform"
>
  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" is:inline set:html={JSON.stringify(dataset)} />

  <main>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="page-panel glass">
          <div class="eyebrow page-kicker">IP geolocation database</div>
          <h1>IP geolocation database downloads for local hosting and repeatable workflows.</h1>
          <p class="page-intro">ProdIPData publishes monthly IP geolocation datasets and browser-based views that help teams work from stable release snapshots instead of ad hoc lookups. The goal is straightforward: make country, ASN, and registry intelligence easier to review, download, and integrate into internal systems.</p>
          <p class="page-intro seo-links">Start with the <a href="downloads.html">downloads hub</a>, compare countries on the <a href="coverage.html">interactive coverage page</a>, review the <a href="ip-geolocation-csv-download.html">CSV download guide</a>, or read the <a href="ip-geolocation-parquet-download.html">Parquet download guide</a> for analytics-oriented use.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container grid-3">
        <article class="section-card glass">
          <h3>Monthly release snapshots</h3>
          <p class="card-text">Each publication is organized around a monthly release label so teams can work from a stable IP geolocation snapshot across the website, local files, reporting jobs, and downstream analysis.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="section-card glass">
          <h3>Country, ASN, and registry context</h3>
          <p class="card-text">The data experience extends beyond approximate location. Country footprint, ASN counts, leading networks, and regional registry views help users understand the visible structure behind the published internet footprint.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="section-card glass">
          <h3>Local-file friendly delivery</h3>
          <p class="card-text">CSV, Parquet, and MMDB packages make it easier to host the files inside your own environment, eliminate per-query dependencies, and integrate IP geolocation data into existing workflows.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container story-grid">
        <div class="split-panel glass content">
          <h2>What a ProdIPData IP geolocation database helps you do</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Review country-level internet footprint and operator context without building a custom dashboard first.</li>
            <li>Use local files in SQL, spreadsheets, Python, data preparation flows, or internal reporting pipelines.</li>
            <li>Compare country structure, concentration, and registry distribution through browser-based views before downloading anything.</li>
            <li>Work from a documented monthly release when reproducibility matters across teams or environments.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="split-panel glass content">
          <h2>Where to start</h2>
          <p>Most users begin with the path that matches their workload.</p>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="ip-geolocation-csv-download.html">Use CSV downloads</a> for spreadsheets, SQL imports, audits, and operational workflows.</li>
            <li><a href="ip-geolocation-parquet-download.html">Use Parquet downloads</a> for analytics, batch processing, and columnar workflows.</li>
            <li><a href="asn-data-by-country.html">Use ASN data by country</a> when the primary question is operator presence and market structure.</li>
            <li><a href="ip-geolocation-data.html">Use the IP geolocation data guide</a> for a plain-language explanation of what the published data represents.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="actions">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="downloads.html">Open downloads hub</a>
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="coverage.html">Explore coverage</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-head">
          <div><h2>Related IP geolocation guides</h2></div>
          <p>These evergreen entry pages target common questions that users bring to a IP geolocation data website.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="download-grid">
          <article class="section-card glass"><h3><a href="ip-geolocation-data.html">IP geolocation data</a></h3><p class="card-text">Understand what IP geolocation data means in practice and how to interpret country, ASN, and registry signals.</p></article>
          <article class="section-card glass"><h3><a href="asn-data-by-country.html">ASN data by country</a></h3><p class="card-text">Focus on country-level operator footprint, leading networks, and concentration views.</p></article>
          <article class="section-card glass"><h3><a href="ip-geolocation-csv-download.html">IP geolocation CSV downloads</a></h3><p class="card-text">Choose CSV files for simple ingestion and human-readable release snapshots.</p></article>
          <article class="section-card glass"><h3><a href="ip-geolocation-parquet-download.html">IP geolocation Parquet downloads</a></h3><p class="card-text">Choose Parquet files for analytics pipelines, batch work, and larger-scale processing.</p></article>
          <article class="section-card glass"><h3><a href="methodology.html">Methodology</a></h3><p class="card-text">Read how monthly releases are assembled and why release-based publication matters.</p></article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
